    lesson: 'Intolerance of uncertainty is a difficulty tolerating the discomfort of not knowing, and it is a strong engine of chronic worry. It drives reassurance-seeking, over-checking, over-researching, and procrastination, all attempts to remove uncertainty that can never be fully removed. Building tolerance for "I don\'t know yet, and that\'s okay" is often a treatment target, frequently with a professional\'s guidance.',
