    lesson: 'Decatastrophizing tests a worst-case thought instead of accepting it. Useful questions: How likely is this really? What is the realistic worst case, the best case, and the most likely case? And crucially, even if the bad thing happened, could I cope? This reaches a balanced, evidence-based appraisal, not forced positivity. It is a skill that improves with practice and can be learned with a therapist.',
